---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { Icon } from "astro-icon/components";
---

<Layout>
  <main
    class="relative min-h-svh flex flex-col justify-center px-6 max-w-2xl mx-auto"
  >
    <div
      class="fixed top-1/2 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 w-150 h-150 bg-amber-400/10 blur-[120px] pointer-events-none -z-10"
    >
    </div>

    <div class="relative z-10 animate-fade-in-up py-20">
      <h1
        class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold tracking-tight mb-8 text-white text-center"
      >
        <span
          class="block text-8xl md:text-9xl text-amber-400 drop-shadow-[0_0_15px_rgba(251,191,36,0.6)] mb-2 md:mb-4"
        >
          404
        </span>
        Wrong Turn?
      </h1>

      <div
        class="space-y-4 text-base md:text-lg text-neutral-400 mb-10 leading-relaxed text-left"
      >
        <p class="indent-8">
          We've searched high and low, but the page you're looking for seems to
          have gotten lost in the vast expanse of the internet.
        </p>
        <p class="indent-8">
          It might be hiding behind a particularly stubborn firewall, or perhaps
          it's taking a much-needed vacation on a remote server farm somewhere
          in the cloud.
        </p>
        <p class="indent-8">
          While we send out a search party, why not head back home? You might
          just stumble upon something even better than what you were originally
          looking for.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="flex justify-center">
        <a
          href="/"
          class="inline-flex px-8 py-3 rounded-full bg-white text-black font-bold hover:scale-105 transition-transform duration-300 items-center gap-2"
        >
          <Icon name="lucide:arrow-left" class="w-5 h-5" />
          Back to Home
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
